reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars For the price this is a steal!! Love my desk.
reviews.reviewText: First off you have to take in consideration the price point. I wanted a small functional desk. I personally had no issues at all putting it together. The pieces are on the thinner side but pretty sturdy still. Its a perfect and functional desk for a small area. This is exactly what I wanted and needed. It has the bottom shelf for a printer or storage. I absolutely love it. If you want a small, sturdy inexpensive desk. This is it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I loved it
reviews.reviewText: This was super easy to assemble. At the time I was sharing a house with many people so my wfh job required me to be outside of the home in order to reduce background noise. And because I live in a high humidity climate I hate to report that the growth of mildew was pretty expensive on the back untreated sides of this desk It required regular maintenance and wiping to keep it cleared but eventually the wood did finally swell and split. But this was to be expected giving the harsh conditions I subjected it to. Overall super happy and if the need was there I would buy this again without hesitation

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute desk for the price
reviews.reviewText: This is a really cute desk - perfect size and price for what I was looking for and needed. The only downside of this is that assembling the desk is a bit confusing. Some of my pieces weren't labeled correctly and I was missing a couple of screws, so that made it a little hard to assemble. I would recommend having wood glue on hand as a back up as well to make sure the legs of the desk are sturdy. It's definitely good and cute for the price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars It Is Cheap
reviews.reviewText: So, if you consider that I spent $30 for a desk, it was a good purchase. It fits in the small space I needed it for, and it holds my laptop (just barely).But, if you consider that I purchased a new desk, the way that it arrived was disappointing. Almost every piece of this desk had minor scuffs or imperfections in the wood. Many of the pieces were missing the letter labels, making building it take longer than it should've. The instructions are in broken English in parts, and some steps were confusing, causing me to put some pieces of this desk together upside down.Overall, it works for a temporary desk, but it is certainly not sturdy or pretty to look at.On the bright side, the "java" color I ordered actually came more black, which is what I originally wanted.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for Smaller Office Spaces
reviews.reviewText: We had a small corner of the room we were looking to add a desk to, for small tasks.The desk is large enough to fit a full sized laptop on it, with room on the top shelf to put a lamp and other stationary accessories.It's the perfect hight for a small stool or chair, but if you have a chair with arms it won't fit under the desk when you move forward.Well made - still looks new even after being in a high traffic area of our house.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for the price
reviews.reviewText: It’s not the best material but you get what you paid

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: For the price of small vanity/computer desk, I love it.. but if I can put a price on time and labor, it all depends on skill set and comprehension.. if you’re retired and have all the time to put this together, then buy it, you got nothing to lose.. just follow the diagrams step by step.. my only minor mistake I made was the sliding drawer.. I screwed the hardware on the top side, instead of the bottom side😂🤣😂.. the manual instructions are like puzzles.. but it was a good experience, I didn’t know that I can be a carpenter at 65.. I think can be a Jane of all Trades😂💕✌🏽

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good temporary desk
reviews.reviewText: I've had this desk for 2 years now and it has served me well enough. Great for small spaces and some extra storage space. Unfortunately, it has not held up. After about a year the screws became loose and it started caving in on itself, which is not a surprise considering the price. If you're looking for a quick temporary solution, this desk is great, If you want something more long term, I suggest making the investment elsewhere.

reviews.reviewTitle: You have what you pay for but it's a very good product
reviews.reviewText: Everything was well packaged and no missing parts.As some said earlier, it is not a very sturdy desk and you should use your hands for screwing instead of a drill. Also, you should realise that it has no sliding keyboard tray.Anyhow, it is a very good looking and well designed desk.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on September 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The quality is amazing, during the assembly it may feel a little wobbly and not great, but when all out together it looks so lovely and cozy, so sturdy (within the correct weight range). The weight is not too bad, it’s what you would expect for a desk, but the size is perfect, the back extra part does not need to be put on if extra flat space is needed, but even with it added, there is so much space. Can fit an a4 piece of paper length ways between the end of the desk to the bump out for the extra compartments. The footrest, under part is an amazing added touch, although sometimes feel like it is a little less sturdy, so maybe put something under it although there is a beam under it. The labelling for the parts to assemble is decent, in some areas the instructions are hard to understand, but with a little common sense you can easily assemble it. The screws are a little fiddly though. For £57 (or £34 if on sale) it is defo worth it, a must buy. The colour is beautiful, size is amazing, so spacious, and such a perfect added touch to any room!
